-- Italy’s Gasoline Demand Drops 6.9% in June, Ministry Data Show
-- B y   N i d a a   B a k h s h
-- 2012-07-12T12:28:35Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-12/italy-s-gasoline-demand-drops-6-9-in-june-ministry-data-show.html
Italy’s gasoline consumption dropped
6.9 percent in June versus a year earlier, according to data
from the  Ministry of Economic Development .  Use of the motor fuel fell to 771,000 metric tons last
month, down from 828,000 tons a year earlier, the data shows.  Diesel and gasoil demand fell 6.8 percent to 2.33 million
tons, according to the data. The country’s total fuels demand
declined 8.4 percent to 5.48 million tons, the data shows.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nidaa Bakhsh in London at 
